abstract: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
snippet: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
lead_paragraph: Steph Davis and Ian Mitchard met at various air sports events and gatherings over the years but did not fall in love until the late fall of 2013 when both were car camping and sky diving near Skydive Arizona in Eloy, Ariz. She was sleeping in her Honda Fit and he in the green rusty van he called home at the time. On a few of their early dates, they cooked dinner together in his van. “I had no kitchen so she brought the stove,” he said.

abstract: The special counsel is investigating whether Mr. Stone, a self-described “dirty trickster,” knew in advance about email releases damaging to Hillary Clinton’s campaign or was merely hyping himself.
snippet: The special counsel is investigating whether Mr. Stone, a self-described “dirty trickster,” knew in advance about email releases damaging to Hillary Clinton’s campaign or was merely hyping himself.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When the WikiLeaks founder, Julian Assange, appeared on a video link from Europe a month before the 2016 presidential election and vaguely promised to release a flood of purloined documents related to the race, the head of Donald J. Trump’s campaign, Stephen K. Bannon, was interested.

abstract: At Henry, a hotel restaurant in Midtown, the chef JJ Johnson’s cooking has a global vision.
snippet: At Henry, a hotel restaurant in Midtown, the chef JJ Johnson’s cooking has a global vision.
lead_paragraph: Earlier this year Henry, a new restaurant in the lobby of the Life Hotel on West 31st Street, quietly died. You wouldn’t know it to look around the place on any recent night at 8, when a seamless playlist of hip-hop and R&B unspools as servers carry stacked beef ribs to what seems like every third table.

abstract: While Jews everywhere expressed shock, the slaughter also surfaced rifts tearing at Israeli society and driving a wedge between Israeli and American Jews.
snippet: While Jews everywhere expressed shock, the slaughter also surfaced rifts tearing at Israeli society and driving a wedge between Israeli and American Jews.
lead_paragraph: BEIT SHEMESH, Israel — The slaughter of 11 Jews in Pittsburgh elicited responses in Israel that echoed the reactions to anti-Semitic killings in Paris, Toulouse and Brussels: expressions of sympathy, reminders that hatred of Jews is as rampant as ever, reaffirmations of the need for a strong Israel.

headline_print_headline: Massacre Exposes Fractures in Jewish Solidarity in Israel and America

abstract: The nation-state of the Jews must recognize Conservative and Reform Judaism.
snippet: The nation-state of the Jews must recognize Conservative and Reform Judaism.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — The massacre of 11 worshipers in a Pittsburgh synagogue has profoundly shocked Israelis. Though seemingly desensitized by years of terror on our buses and streets, much of this voluble country has been left speechless by the news of Jews being gunned down during Shabbat prayers by a ranting anti-Semite.
